"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-paris-hopes-security-wont-spoil-the-party-at-2024-olympics-opening\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  FILE PHOTO: Paris 2024 Olympics - Paris, France - July 21, 2024 A police officer and a sniffer dog inspect a swimming pool area ahead of the Olympics REUTERS/Gonzalo Fuentes/File Photo    PublishedJul 22, 2024, 12:59 AM  UpdatedJul 22, 2024, 12:59 AM  PARIS - As Paris makes final preparations for the Summer Olympics, the grand opening ceremony along the river Seine on Friday has created an unprecedented security challenge that organisers hope will not dampen the party vibe.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.028385775569352e-12, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998714712342447, \"rank\": 8.060290293259462e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 389, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 397, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gonzalo_Pizarro\", \"score\": 0.9883141465288988, \"rank\": 0.010930586347636396, \"text\": \"Gonzalo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gonzalo_Pizarro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gonzalo_Pizarro\"}, {\"begin\": 405, \"end\": 412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Fuentes\", \"score\": 0.9999999994192876, \"rank\": 5.806069423360717e-10, \"text\": \"Fuentes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Fuentes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Fuentes\"}, {\"begin\": 502, \"end\": 507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.093294937215571e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time, a Games opening ceremony will not take place in a stadium.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, dozens of boats will carry thousands of athletes and performers on a 6-km (3.7-mile) floating parade down the Seine, showcasing the beauty and history of the French capital.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 917, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 7.596883126874443e-12, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 965, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7663186120401151, \"rank\": 0.21842302054975485, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 300,000 people are expected to line both banks of the river to watch the ceremony - along with 45,000 police, including members of France's elite special intervention forces trained in counterterrorism.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1123, \"end\": 1129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998714712342447, \"rank\": 8.060290293259462e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Snipers will be deployed on the top of buildings along the route and an anti-drone system will be in place.\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a balance to be found between top security, which is absolutely the priority,\\\" Tony Estanguet, president of the Paris 2024 organising committee, told a press conference on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1427, \"end\": 1437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1768561406776544e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's part of the objective to guarantee the security and to propose a fantastic celebration of the Games...\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But to have this kind of unique celebration, you also need to have a very, very strong security plan.\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's the case.\\\"\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony, which will start at 7:30 p.m. local time(1730 GMT), will be \\\"a large fresco\\\" celebrating Paris, France and the Games and will interweave the traditional parade by athletes with artistic performances and elements of protocol, said Thomas Jolly, the artistic director of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 2034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.732139370196735e-15, \"text\": \"GMT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\"}, {\"begin\": 1833, \"end\": 1838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.093294937215571e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998714712342447, \"rank\": 8.060290293259462e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1974, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.6830955000928979, \"rank\": 0.44525835620304954, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With wars in Gaza and Ukraine, and security concerns at home, France is already at its highest level of security.\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2049, \"end\": 2053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\", \"score\": 0.8202686622235713, \"rank\": 0.21911276884399258, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_City\"}, {\"begin\": 2058, \"end\": 2065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9998828293957195, \"rank\": 8.375911655672507e-05, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2098, \"end\": 2104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998714712342447, \"rank\": 8.060290293259462e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowds set to descend on Paris will be in marked contrast to the atmosphere of the last Summer Olympics in Tokyo in 2021 which played to empty arenas, and a year later than scheduled, due to the COVID-19 pandemic.\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2179, \"end\": 2184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.093294937215571e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2261, \"end\": 2266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999963038135, \"rank\": 2.9556440497518446e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics